{
  "$schema": "https://json.schemastore.org/claude-code-settings.json",
  "_description": "AcceptEdits profile — daily development working mode. File edits and routine dev commands run without prompting. Ask is reserved for genuinely consequential mutations: production deploys, infrastructure create/delete, external message dispatch. Deny is the safety floor. For scratch/MVP work, use bypass profile. For high-stakes review work, use default profile.",
  "_safety_notes": [
    "acceptEdits ≠ default. Day-to-day dev (pip install, docker compose up, aws s3 cp, git rebase, rm -rf node_modules, brew install, kubectl apply on dev cluster) does NOT prompt. If ask fires more than a few times per hour, the profile is too tight — promote items to allow.",
    "Ask is reserved for: infrastructure create/delete with cost or data impact, production schema deploys, external message dispatch (SES), deployment actions that shift traffic.",
    "The real safety boundary for prod vs dev is environment isolation (AWS_PROFILE, kubectl context, DATABASE_URL), not ask prompts. Set those up and ask can shrink further.",
    "Bash(env) and friends are denied: prevents ANTHROPIC_API_KEY leakage into conversation context.",
    "Compound bash (&&, ;, ||, |, eval, bash -c, command substitution) is denied to prevent allow/deny bypass via chaining. This is the policy backbone.",
    "Self-modification of CLAUDE.md and .claude/** is denied — change those outside Claude Code. .harness/** is allowed because it is the working surface for harness automation."
  ],
